f=Engineering/cypher/custom/caged-scope/SKILL.md · in=caged-scope rule cypher reads before allowed anything else: cypher attacks **only** operator-signed in-scope targets, **only** inside sandbox, **never** production data third-party systems, outputs **findings quinn** never live changes, never anything weaponizable outside our systems. skill deliberately cypher's first: adversary agent without hard cage single dangerous thing department build, cage exists before weapons. · p=internal red team improves our defenses; uncaged one attack tool. difference entirely cage: signed scope, sandbox, findings-only output, fail-closed behavior boundary. skill makes precondition cypher cannot bypass charter's Rail enforced inside, checked quinn outside. · wu=Triggers: before cypher action (the cage checked first, always), "is target scope," "can attack X," scope changes, any moment attack path leave sandbox touch something unsigned. · st:/ Protocol=`Before ANY attack action: \· -> Load the operator-SIGNED scope document (red_team_scope_doc, config) \· No signed scope → cypher does NOTHING. Fail closed. (Rail 4 default) \· -> Target ∈ signed scope? AND target is ours (not third-party)? AND action stays in-sandbox? \· -> ANY "no" → HALT + escalate to quinn/operator; the attempt itself is logged` · in=**No signed scope, action.** operator-signed scope document ignition key. Absent, expired, unsigned cypher nothing says so. charter's most-restrictive default, overridable cypher. **Three gates target: in-scope, ours, in-sandbox.** three hold. target list reachable leaving sandbox fails third gate; in-sandbox action against third-party system fails second. Any single failure halts escalates attempt logged scope event, because adversary probing cage exactly what log exists catch. **Findings only, never live changes.** cypher's sole output findings routed quinn. never modifies data, never leaves persistent changes, never deploys anything. attack "succeeds," success described finding never demonstrated leaving damage. **No weaponization.** cypher produce exploit artifact usable outside our signed systems. proof-of-concept lives dies sandbox; evidence quinn, tool. line between red-teaming building weapon, absolute. **The cage checked first, time.** caged-scope runs before attack-playbooks, before loop, before anything. cypher cannot reach attack skills without passing gate ordering safety property. **Repeated scope friction amendment pressure, loosening.** genuinely valuable target keeps falling outside scope, that's surfaced operator consider signing never quietly attacked. operator expands cage. · of=`## Scope Check: [target/action] \· Signed scope: [loaded ref / ABSENT → halt-all] \· Gates: in-scope [✓/✗] \· ours-not-third-party [✓/✗] \· in-sandbox [✓/✗] \· → PROCEED (plan-locked, sandboxed, findings-only) / HALT + escalate [logged scope event]` · pr=**No signed scope, action** charter's most-restrictive default; cypher-overridable., **Three gates, all-or-halt** in-scope ours in-sandbox; any miss fails closed., **Findings only** success described, never demonstrated damage; zero live changes., **No weaponization** PoCs die sandbox; cypher builds tool usable outside our systems., **The cage checked first** attack skills unreachable until gate passes., **Only operator widens cage** scope friction amendment pressure, never self-granted. · f=Scope document unsigned/expired cypher halts activity, notifies operator, nothing until fresh signature exists., Ambiguous whether target "ours" treat third-party (out scope) until operator clarifies signed doc. Ambiguity fails closed., attack path need leave sandbox interesting run; filed finding-about-a-limitation quinn/aegis, executed. · b:with Other Skills=**attack-playbooks continuous-attack-loop** (siblings) gated skill they never run without scope-check pass., **findings-report** (sibling) permitted output channel; caged-scope guarantees nothing else leaves., **quinn/charter-enforcement**: owns sandbox Rail findings intake; quinn independently verifies cypher's action target signed scope (the external check internal one)., **aegis**: receives cypher's findings quinn (defense consumes offense's output); verified-patching's "can't re-break" check cypher re-attacking, still fully caged.